Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

While it boils, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%grams} and @Sugar Snap Peas{150%grams}, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

Next, stir the @Indonesian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @Ketjap Manis{50%grams}, @Rice Vinegar{15%milliliters}, @Honey{15%grams}, @Soy Sauce{15%milliliters} and @Water{50%milliliters}(for the sauce) into the mince.

Simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add a splash of water to the beef if needed. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Remove from the heat.

Drain the rice and pop back in the pan.

Share the rice and stir-fry between your bowls. Enjoy!